The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Jan. 14: The government has appointed a panel to suggest ways to encourage investments in the financial sector such as in bonds and the stock market. The working group, headed by U.K. Sinha, chairman of UTI Asset Management Company, will suggest reforms in the sector.                            
	 New Delhi, Jan. 14: The government today relaxed norms for considering domestic supplies to mega power projects as exports. The move will help local suppliers get exports sops. Companies such as Bhel, L amp;T and Bharat Forge will benefit.                             
	 Mumbai, Jan. 14: Citigroup Global sold shares worth Rs 491 crore in 36 Indian companies today, taking the total share sale to Rs 971 crore. Citigroup Global Mauritius sold shares in 36 domestic companies, including RIL, HDFC and Infosys.                            
	 Washington, Jan. 14: US President Barack Obama has proposed Wall Street pay a fee of up to $117 billion to repay taxpayers for the financial bailout, as he slammed bankers for their massive profits and obscene bonuses.                             
	 Mumbai/ New York, Jan. 14: Shares of Wipro slumped 7 per cent on the NYSE today even as the IT major jumped 3 per cent on the domestic bourses, amid reports of its likely launch of a $1-billion sponsored ADR issue.                                                                                                                          
